Lac Minerals Ltd's exploration spendingwill rise this year to 25 mln dlrs from 16.3 mln dlrs lastyear, the company said in its annual report.    The 1987 budget involves 16 mln dlrs for advancedexploration on a tin project in New Brunswick, Bousquet minenumber two in Quebec and the Ortiz property in New Mexico, andnine mln dlrs for pure exploration.    Total capital and exploration spending will rise to about130 mln dlrs from 98 mln dlrs last year, with 77 mln dlrs ofthe 1987 amount set for the Page-Williams mine in Hemlo,Ontario, Lac said.    Lac's total 1986 gold production rose to 478,394 ouncesfrom 265,925 ounces the previous year. Production excludingPage-Williams eased to 245,232 from 255,556 ounces in 1985. Reuter&#3;